title.narrative: NUTRITION(02) MTR - NUTRITION FOR SCHOOL-AGE CHILDREN AND ADOLESCENTS

description.narrative: Nutrition for school-age children, adolescents, and women UNICEF regional offices and country offices have enhanced strategic and technical capacity to support countries in preventing anemia and other forms of malnutrition in adolescent girls and boys, and achieve global targets on reduction of low birth weight., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Adolescent Health And Nutrition (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child to Survive and Thrive By 2021, countries apply child-sensitive policies, innovative community-centered approaches and evidence, to implement development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that enable Every Child to Survive and Thrive
